plot: UK prime ministers kept resigning, making unpopular choices that impacted the country. When Sunak unexpectedly called for elections, it highlighted the nation's turbulent political landscape and consequences of past leadership decisions.

John Oliver talks about the sudden United Kingdom elections announcement by Sunak. He also points out what a series of unpopular leadership they have been gone through for past few years and bad choices by those people is now hurting the whole country.—Niaz Islam Arif
